com.xerox.xrce.codex.jri.model.tracker
Class CxTracker

java.lang.Object
  com.xerox.xrce.codex.jri.model.CxFromServer
      com.xerox.xrce.codex.jri.model.tracker.CxTracker
All Implemented Interfaces:
ITooltipable
public class CxTracker
extends CxFromServer
implements ITooltipable

CxTracker is the class for CodeX Trackers. A CxTracker is a generic object for tracking things (like bugs, tasks, support request, requirements, etc.) The generic objects tracked by the tracker is called artefact (CxArtefact).

getArtifacts

public com.xerox.xrce.codex.jri.model.wsproxy.ArtifactQueryResult getArtifacts(CxCriteria[] criterias,
                                                                               int offset,
                                                                               int max_rows)
                                                                        throws CxException
Returns the ArtifactQueryResult of the tracker that are matching the given criteria. If offset AND max_rows are filled, it returns only max_rows artifacts, skipping the first offset ones. It is not possible to sort artifact with this function (use getArtifactsFromReport if you want to sort). Returns a soap fault if the group_id is not a valid one or if the group_artifact_id is not a valid one.

Parameters:
criterias - the criterias for filtering the artifacts
offset - offset to start the returned results
max_rows - the numbers of returned artefacts
Returns:
the ArtifactQueryResult of the tracker that are matching the given criteria
Throws:
CxException
